issue.title: Crash if tray icon used on Windows 10
issue.body:
### Flameshot Version

Flameshot v13.0.1 (48f8d1fd)
Compiled with Qt 6.8.1
winnt: 10.0.19045
windows: 10

### Installation Type

Linux, MacOS, or Windows Package manager (apt, pacman, eopkg, choco, brew, ...)

### Operating System type and version

Windows 10

### Description

The tool does crash if the tray icon is used multiple times.

You will need to open up a popup menu with your first interaction otherwise it will keep running. In theory it does not matter which dialog you open the behavior is always identically.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Right click tray icon
2. Select about Flameshot
3. Close popup menu
4. Right click tray icon again
5. Flameshot crashing without warning

### Screenshots or screen recordings

_No response_

### System Information

Windows 10 dual HD monitor setup

issue.title: I'm getting 3 errors of "image not found" and "status 400 when atempting to download", what am I doing wrong?
issue.body: basically the title, what am I doing wrong to get these? adding the log just in case. [meta (2).log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21823002/meta.2.log)

comment.body:
1. This image is always a pain to deal with because in the HTTP world, `#` is not a valid character and should be referenced in unicode (i.e. `%230.jpg`). I don't have a good solution for this and since the network is not well known, it's not a priority. It can be ignored.
2. I've added HBO Max to the network overlays, this is likely due to the re-rebrand of Max - 3f8e786
3. I don't yet have a Tubi overlay image to reference, so Kometa shows an error since it can't find it.

None of these are breaking changes but if you have shows using `#0` or `Tubi`, it won't add any overlay for them. I will try to put together a Tubi overlay sometime soon.

issue.title: writeValue sometimes does not return when sending multiple messages

comment.body:
> I tried making a fairly barebones CoreBluetooth client as well that just uses continuations to make it async and it had the same problem. I don't know if it's my peripheral or if there's some queuing or checking that i need to be doing

If your message has a write type `.withoutResponse`, it probably has something to do with `peripheralIsReady(toSendWriteWithoutResponse:)`, since this library doesn't handle that, it may cause hanging after setting complete for writeCharacteristicValueExecutor. For a typical CoreBluetooth application, it will handle that in a kind of loop of resending the data that `failed` since CoreBluetooth has no error callback for that type of message.

Im trying to implement a Peripheral Manager in the same manner, maybe able to fix this along the way. Will update later.

issue.body:
Currently the staff user will go through the page, evaluate the contents and make a decision to approve/disapprove/add label/etc., but to do that they need to scroll back up.

As such, we should

* Introduce an icon pinned to the right edge of the viewport
* When clicked, it opens a modal sidebar, also pinned to the right edge of the viewport
* The sidebar should contain:
  * Approve / remove approval button
  * Current labels and the ability to remove them
  * Button to add another label
  * Field to leave a comment

This exercise will help you learn how to expand GitHub Copilot's capabilities with Model Context Protocol (MCP). --- **This is an interactive, hands-on GitHub Skills exercise!** As you complete each step, Ill leave updates in the comments: - Check your work and guide you forward - Share helpful tips and resources - Celebrate your progress and completion Lets get started - good luck and have fun! Mona

comment.body:
## Step 3: Solve issues with Agent Mode and GitHub MCP Server Great work doing that research and finding a potential collaboration opportunity. Not only did we find some new ideas to help organize extracurricular activities, but we did all that quickly too. Plenty of time to focus on the fun stuff, like teaching our awesome students! On that note, it seems the teachers have also been active. Looks like they submitted some bugs and requests! Perfect! Now, let's use our MCP server's tools and Copilot to do a bit of triage and get some work done. ### :keyboard: Activity: Easily implement an important issue 1. Ensure the **Copilot Chat** panel is open and **Agent** mode is selected. Verify the MCP server tools are also still available. 1. Ask Copilot about the open issues on this repository. > ![Static Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/-Prompt-text?style=social&logo=github%20copilot) > > ```prompt > How many open issues are there on my repository? > ``` > **Note:** Check that the List Issues tool is called with proper parameters. 1. Ask Copilot to summarize the important issues. > ![Static Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/-Prompt-text?style=social&logo=github%20copilot) > > ```prompt > Oh no. That's too many for me! Please get the list of issues, > review the descriptions and comments, and pick the top 3 most important. > ```
Tip: Pre-authorize tool usage
If Copilot uses a tool often, you can proactively grant permission for the rest of the conversation session.
1. Review the suggested issues. If Copilot didn't give a specific recommendation, try providing some feedback to narrow the results. 1. With the list narrowed, ask Copilot to implement an issue. **Mona won't grade if the changes work, just that an attempt was made.** > ![Static Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/-Prompt-text?style=social&logo=github%20copilot) > > ```prompt > #codebase Let's do the first one. Follow these steps: > 1. Checkout a new local branch for making our changes. > 2. Make the changes then confirm with me that they look correct. > 3. Push the changes and start a pull request. > ``` > **Warning:** Always verify the the actions Copilot is asking to perform, especially with the external abilities provided by an MCP server, which probably have no undo option. 1. Once the pull request is created, Mona will start checking your work. Give her a moment and keep watch of the comments. You will see her respond with progress info and the next step!
Having trouble?
- If tools are not being requested, verify your MCP configuration is correct. - If Copilot cannot retrieve results, verify you are using this Codespace's token or a Personal Access Token (PAT) with appropriate permissions. By default, the codespace token we are using only has access to this repository.

pull_request.title: Feat/random improvements 2025 08 17
pull_request.body:
This pull request refactors the codebase to move all decision treerelated modules into a new `models` subpackage, updates all import statements accordingly, and introduces utility functions to handle random sampling of features and samples. It also includes some minor improvements to scikit-learn compatibility and code clarity. The changes affect both the library code and the example notebooks.

**1. Codebase Restructuring and Import Updates**
